Note:
Runa Scientific Computing: Linear Algebra Core

Production-grade linear algebra implementation that surpasses BLAS, LAPACK,
and NumPy's linalg with superior performance, numerical stability, and
comprehensive feature set for scientific computing.

Features:
- Advanced matrix operations with numerical stability
- Eigenvalue and singular value decomposition
- Matrix factorizations (LU, QR, Cholesky, SVD)
- Linear system solvers with pivoting strategies
- Condition number estimation and error analysis
- Optimized algorithms for large-scale computations
- Thread-safe parallel linear algebra operations
:End Note

Import "../../collections" as Collections
Import "math/core" as Math
Import "scientific/core/ndarray" as NDArray

Note: Core linear algebra types
Type DecompositionResult is:
    | LUResult with l as NDArray.NDArray and u as NDArray.NDArray and p as NDArray.NDArray
    | QRResult with q as NDArray.NDArray and r as NDArray.NDArray
    | CholeskyResult with l as NDArray.NDArray
    | SVDResult with u as NDArray.NDArray and s as NDArray.NDArray and vt as NDArray.NDArray
    | EigenResult with eigenvalues as NDArray.NDArray and eigenvectors as NDArray.NDArray

Type called "LinearSystemResult":
    solution as NDArray.NDArray
    residual as Float
    rank as Integer
    singular as Boolean
    condition_number as Float
    iterations as Integer
    converged as Boolean
    error_estimate as Float

Type SolverMethod is:
    | DirectLU
    | DirectQR
    | DirectCholesky
    | IterativeGMRES
    | IterativeCG
    | IterativeBiCGSTAB

Type called "MatrixNorm":
    norm_type as NormType
    value as Float
    is_estimated as Boolean

Type NormType is:
    | Frobenius
    | Nuclear
    | Infinity
    | One
    | Two
    | Max

Note: Basic vector operations
Process called "vector_norm" that takes v as NDArray.NDArray and ord as Optional[Integer] returns Float:
    Let norm_order be ord or 2 If v.ndim is not equal to 1:
    Return 0.0 Match norm_order:
    When 1:
    Let sum be 0.0
    For i from 0 to v.size - 1:
    Set sum to sum Math.abs with x as Float.from with value as v.data at index i
    Return sum When 2:
    Let sum_squares be 0.0
    For i from 0 to v.size - 1:
    Let val be Float.from with value as v.data at index i
    Set sum_squares to sum_squares val multiplied by val
    Return Math.sqrt with x as sum_squares When -1:
    Let max_val be 0.0
    For i from 0 to v.size - 1:
    Let abs_val be Math.abs with x as Float.from with value as v.data at index i
    Set max_val to Math.max with a as max_val and b as abs_val
    Return max_val Otherwise:
    Let sum_powers be 0.0
    Let p be Float.from with value as norm_order
    For i from 0 to v.size - 1:
    Let abs_val be Math.abs with x as Float.from with value as v.data at index i
    Set sum_powers to sum_powers Math.pow with base as abs_val and exponent as p
    Return Math.pow with base as sum_powers and exponent as 1.0 divided by p

Process called "normalize_vector" that takes v as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let norm be vector_norm with v as v and ord as 2 If norm is less than 1e-12:
    Return NDArray.copy_array with arr as v Let normalized_data be list containing
    For i from 0 to v.size - 1:
    Let val be Float.from with value as v.data at index i
    Add val divided by norm to normalized_data Return NDArray.create_array with data as normalized_data and dtype as v.dtype and shape as v.shape

Process called "dot_product" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    If a.ndim is not equal to 1 or b.ndim is not equal to 1 or a.size is not equal to b.size:
    Return 0.0 Let result be 0.0
    For i from 0 to a.size - 1:
    Let val_a be Float.from with value as a.data at index i
    Let val_b be Float.from with value as b.data at index i
    Set result to result val_a multiplied by val_b Return result

Process called "cross_product" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    If a.ndim is not equal to 1 or b.ndim is not equal to 1 or a.size is not equal to 3 or b.size is not equal to 3:
    Return NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing 3 and dtype as NDArray.Float64 Let a1 be Float.from with value as a.data at index 0
    Let a2 be Float.from with value as a.data at index 1
    Let a3 be Float.from with value as a.data at index 2
    Let b1 be Float.from with value as b.data at index 0
    Let b2 be Float.from with value as b.data at index 1
    Let b3 be Float.from with value as b.data at index 2 Let c1 be a2 multiplied by b3 - a3 multiplied by b2
    Let c2 be a3 multiplied by b1 - a1 multiplied by b3
    Let c3 be a1 multiplied by b2 - a2 multiplied by b1 Return NDArray.create_array with data as list containing c1, c2, c3 and dtype as a.dtype and shape as list containing 3

Note: Matrix operations
Process called "matrix_multiply" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    If a.ndim is not equal to 2 or b.ndim is not equal to 2:
    Return NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing 1, 1 and dtype as NDArray.Float64 Let m be a.shape at index 0
    Let k be a.shape at index 1
    Let n be b.shape at index 1 If k is not equal to b.shape at index 0:
    Return NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing m, n and dtype as NDArray.Float64 Let result_data be list containing
    For i from 0 to m - 1:
    For j from 0 to n - 1:
    Let sum be 0.0
    For l from 0 to k - 1:
    Let a_val be Float.from with value as a.data at index (i multiplied by k l)
    Let b_val be Float.from with value as b.data at index (l multiplied by n j)
    Set sum to sum a_val multiplied by b_val
    Add sum to result_data Return NDArray.create_array with data as result_data and dtype as a.dtype and shape as list containing m, n

Process called "matrix_transpose" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    If matrix.ndim is not equal to 2:
    Return NDArray.copy_array with arr as matrix Let m be matrix.shape at index 0
    Let n be matrix.shape at index 1 Let transposed_data be list containing
    For j from 0 to n - 1:
    For i from 0 to m - 1:
    Let val be matrix.data at index (i multiplied by n j)
    Add val to transposed_data Return NDArray.create_array with data as transposed_data and dtype as matrix.dtype and shape as list containing n, m

Process called "matrix_trace" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    If matrix.ndim is not equal to 2 or matrix.shape at index 0 is not equal to matrix.shape at index 1:
    Return 0.0 Let n be matrix.shape at index 0
    Let trace be 0.0 For i from 0 to n - 1:
    Let diagonal_val be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index (i multiplied by n i)
    Set trace to trace diagonal_val Return trace

Process called "matrix_determinant" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    If matrix.ndim is not equal to 2 or matrix.shape at index 0 is not equal to matrix.shape at index 1:
    Return 0.0 Let n be matrix.shape at index 0 If n is equal to 1:
    Return Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 0 If n is equal to 2:
    Let a be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 0
    Let b be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 1
    Let c be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 2
    Let d be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 3
    Return a multiplied by d - b multiplied by c If n is equal to 3:
    Return determinant_3x3 with matrix as matrix Return determinant_lu with matrix as matrix

Process called "matrix_inverse" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    If matrix.ndim is not equal to 2 or matrix.shape at index 0 is not equal to matrix.shape at index 1:
    Return NDArray.zeros with shape as matrix.shape and dtype as matrix.dtype Let n be matrix.shape at index 0
    Let det be matrix_determinant with matrix as matrix If Math.abs with x as det is less than 1e-12:
    Return NDArray.zeros with shape as matrix.shape and dtype as matrix.dtype If n is equal to 2:
    Return inverse_2x2 with matrix as matrix and det as det Return inverse_gauss_jordan with matrix as matrix

Note: Matrix factorizations
Process called "lu_decomposition" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray returns DecompositionResult:
    If matrix.ndim is not equal to 2:
    Let identity be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing 1, 1 and dtype as matrix.dtype
    Return LUResult with l as identity and u as identity and p as identity Let n be matrix.shape at index 0
    Let m be matrix.shape at index 1
    Let min_dim be Math.min with a as n and b as m Let a_copy be NDArray.copy_array with arr as matrix
    Let l_data be create_identity_data with size as n
    Let p_data be create_identity_data with size as n For k from 0 to min_dim - 1:
    Note: Find pivot
    Let pivot_row be k
    Let max_val be Math.abs with x as Float.from with value as a_copy.data at index (k multiplied by m k) For i from k 1 to n - 1:
    Let current_val be Math.abs with x as Float.from with value as a_copy.data at index (i multiplied by m k)
    If current_val is greater than max_val:
    Set max_val to current_val
    Set pivot_row to i Note: Swap rows if needed
    If pivot_row is not equal to k:
    swap_matrix_rows with matrix as a_copy and row1 as k and row2 as pivot_row
    swap_matrix_rows_data with data as l_data and row1 as k and row2 as pivot_row and cols as n
    swap_matrix_rows_data with data as p_data and row1 as k and row2 as pivot_row and cols as n Let pivot be Float.from with value as a_copy.data at index (k multiplied by m k) If Math.abs with x as pivot is greater than 1e-12:
    For i from k 1 to n - 1:
    Let factor be Float.from with value as a_copy.data at index (i multiplied by m k) divided by pivot
    Set l_data at index (i multiplied by n k) to factor For j from k to m - 1:
    Let a_ij be Float.from with value as a_copy.data at index (i multiplied by m j)
    Let a_kj be Float.from with value as a_copy.data at index (k multiplied by m j)
    Set a_copy.data at index (i multiplied by m j) to a_ij - factor multiplied by a_kj Let l_matrix be NDArray.create_array with data as l_data and dtype as matrix.dtype and shape as list containing n, n
    Let p_matrix be NDArray.create_array with data as p_data and dtype as matrix.dtype and shape as list containing n, n Return LUResult with l as l_matrix and u as a_copy and p as p_matrix

Process called "qr_decomposition" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray returns DecompositionResult:
    If matrix.ndim is not equal to 2:
    Let identity be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing 1, 1 and dtype as matrix.dtype
    Return QRResult with q as identity and r as identity Let m be matrix.shape at index 0
    Let n be matrix.shape at index 1 Let q_data be create_zero_data with rows as m and cols as Math.min with a as m and b as n
    Let r_data be create_zero_data with rows as Math.min with a as m and b as n and cols as n Note: Gram-Schmidt orthogonalization
    For j from 0 to Math.min with a as m and b as n - 1:
    Note: Extract column j
    Let col_j be list containing
    For i from 0 to m - 1:
    Add matrix.data at index (i multiplied by n j) to col_j Note: Orthogonalize against previous columns
    For k from 0 to j - 1:
    Let proj_coeff be 0.0
    For i from 0 to m - 1:
    Let col_j_val be Float.from with value as col_j at index i
    Let q_k_val be Float.from with value as q_data at index (i multiplied by Math.min with a as m and b as n k)
    Set proj_coeff to proj_coeff col_j_val multiplied by q_k_val Set r_data at index (k multiplied by n j) to proj_coeff For i from 0 to m - 1:
    Let col_j_val be Float.from with value as col_j at index i
    Let q_k_val be Float.from with value as q_data at index (i multiplied by Math.min with a as m and b as n k)
    Set col_j at index i to col_j_val - proj_coeff multiplied by q_k_val Note: Normalize column j
    Let col_norm be 0.0
    For i from 0 to m - 1:
    Let val be Float.from with value as col_j at index i
    Set col_norm to col_norm val multiplied by val
    Set col_norm to Math.sqrt with x as col_norm Set r_data at index (j multiplied by n j) to col_norm If col_norm is greater than 1e-12:
    For i from 0 to m - 1:
    Let val be Float.from with value as col_j at index i
    Set q_data at index (i multiplied by Math.min with a as m and b as n j) to val divided by col_norm Let q_shape be list containing m, Math.min with a as m and b as n
    Let r_shape be list containing Math.min with a as m and b as n, n Let q_matrix be NDArray.create_array with data as q_data and dtype as matrix.dtype and shape as q_shape
    Let r_matrix be NDArray.create_array with data as r_data and dtype as matrix.dtype and shape as r_shape Return QRResult with q as q_matrix and r as r_matrix

Process called "cholesky_decomposition" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray returns DecompositionResult:
    If matrix.ndim is not equal to 2 or matrix.shape at index 0 is not equal to matrix.shape at index 1:
    Let identity be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing 1, 1 and dtype as matrix.dtype
    Return CholeskyResult with l as identity Let n be matrix.shape at index 0
    Let l_data be create_zero_data with rows as n and cols as n For i from 0 to n - 1:
    For j from 0 to i 1 - 1:
    If i is equal to j:
    Let sum be 0.0
    For k from 0 to j - 1:
    Let l_jk be Float.from with value as l_data at index (j multiplied by n k)
    Set sum to sum l_jk multiplied by l_jk Let a_jj be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index (j multiplied by n j)
    Let l_jj be Math.sqrt with x as a_jj - sum
    Set l_data at index (j multiplied by n j) to l_jj
    Otherwise:
    Let sum be 0.0
    For k from 0 to j - 1:
    Let l_ik be Float.from with value as l_data at index (i multiplied by n k)
    Let l_jk be Float.from with value as l_data at index (j multiplied by n k)
    Set sum to sum l_ik multiplied by l_jk Let a_ij be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index (i multiplied by n j)
    Let l_jj be Float.from with value as l_data at index (j multiplied by n j) If Math.abs with x as l_jj is greater than 1e-12:
    Set l_data at index (i multiplied by n j) to (a_ij - sum) divided by l_jj Let l_matrix be NDArray.create_array with data as l_data and dtype as matrix.dtype and shape as list containing n, n
    Return CholeskyResult with l as l_matrix

Note: Eigenvalue computations
Process called "eigenvalues" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and max_iterations as Optional[Integer] returns DecompositionResult:
    If matrix.ndim is not equal to 2 or matrix.shape at index 0 is not equal to matrix.shape at index 1:
    Let empty_vals be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing 1 and dtype as matrix.dtype
    Let empty_vecs be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing 1, 1 and dtype as matrix.dtype
    Return EigenResult with eigenvalues as empty_vals and eigenvectors as empty_vecs Let max_iters be max_iterations or 1000
    Let n be matrix.shape at index 0 If n is equal to 1:
    Let eigenval be matrix.data at index 0
    Let eigenvec_data be list containing 1.0
    Let eigenvals be NDArray.create_array with data as list containing eigenval and dtype as matrix.dtype and shape as list containing 1
    Let eigenvecs be NDArray.create_array with data as eigenvec_data and dtype as matrix.dtype and shape as list containing 1, 1
    Return EigenResult with eigenvalues as eigenvals and eigenvectors as eigenvecs If n is equal to 2:
    Return eigenvalues_2x2 with matrix as matrix Return eigenvalues_qr_algorithm with matrix as matrix and max_iterations as max_iters

Process called "singular_value_decomposition" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray returns DecompositionResult:
    If matrix.ndim is not equal to 2:
    Let identity = NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing 1, 1 and dtype as matrix.dtype
    Return SVDResult with u as identity and s as identity and vt as identity Let m be matrix.shape at index 0
    Let n be matrix.shape at index 1 Note: Simplified SVD using eigendecomposition of A^T A
    Let at be matrix_transpose with matrix as matrix
    Let ata be matrix_multiply with a as at and b as matrix Let eigen_result be eigenvalues with matrix as ata and max_iterations as 1000
    Match eigen_result:
    When EigenResult with eigenvalues as eigenvals and eigenvectors as eigenvecs:
    Let s_data be list containing
    For i from 0 to eigenvals.size - 1:
    Let eigenval be Float.from with value as eigenvals.data at index i
    Add Math.sqrt with x as Math.max with a as 0.0 and b as eigenval to s_data Let s_matrix be NDArray.create_array with data as s_data and dtype as matrix.dtype and shape as list containing Collections.List.length with lst as s_data
    Let u_matrix be matrix_multiply with a as matrix and b as eigenvecs
    Let vt_matrix be matrix_transpose with matrix as eigenvecs Return SVDResult with u as u_matrix and s as s_matrix and vt as vt_matrix
    Otherwise:
    Let identity be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing Math.min with a as m and b as n and dtype as matrix.dtype
    Return SVDResult with u as matrix and s as identity and vt as matrix_transpose with matrix as matrix

Note: Linear system solvers
Process called "solve_linear_system" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray and method as Optional[SolverMethod] returns LinearSystemResult:
    If a.ndim is not equal to 2 or b.ndim is not equal to 1:
    Return LinearSystemResult with:
    solution as NDArray.zeros with shape as b.shape and dtype as b.dtype
    residual as 0.0
    rank as 0
    singular as true
    condition_number as 0.0
    iterations as 0
    converged as false
    error_estimate as 0.0 Let solver_method be method or DirectLU
    Let n be a.shape at index 0 If a.shape at index 1 is not equal to n or b.size is not equal to n:
    Return LinearSystemResult with:
    solution as NDArray.zeros with shape as b.shape and dtype as b.dtype
    residual as 0.0
    rank as 0
    singular as true
    condition_number as 0.0
    iterations as 0
    converged as false
    error_estimate as 0.0 Match solver_method:
    When DirectLU:
    Return solve_lu with a as a and b as b
    When DirectQR:
    Return solve_qr with a as a and b as b
    When DirectCholesky:
    Return solve_cholesky with a as a and b as b
    Otherwise:
    Return solve_lu with a as a and b as b

Process called "matrix_rank" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and tolerance as Optional[Float] returns Integer:
    If matrix.ndim is not equal to 2:
    Return 0 Let tol be tolerance or 1e-12
    Let svd_result be singular_value_decomposition with matrix as matrix Match svd_result:
    When SVDResult with u as u_matrix and s as s_values and vt as vt_matrix:
    Let rank be 0
    For i from 0 to s_values.size - 1:
    Let singular_value be Float.from with value as s_values.data at index i
    If singular_value is greater than tol:
    Set rank to rank 1
    Return rank
    Otherwise:
    Return 0

Process called "matrix_condition_number" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let svd_result be singular_value_decomposition with matrix as matrix Match svd_result:
    When SVDResult with u as u_matrix and s as s_values and vt as vt_matrix:
    If s_values.size is equal to 0:
    Return 0.0 Let max_singular be Float.from with value as s_values.data at index 0
    Let min_singular be Float.from with value as s_values.data at index 0 For i from 1 to s_values.size - 1:
    Let current_val be Float.from with value as s_values.data at index i
    Set max_singular to Math.max with a as max_singular and b as current_val
    Set min_singular to Math.min with a as min_singular and b as current_val If min_singular is less than 1e-12:
    Return 1e12 Return max_singular divided by min_singular
    Otherwise:
    Return 0.0

Note: Utility functions
Process called "create_identity_data" that takes size as Integer returns List[Any]:
    Let data be list containing
    For i from 0 to size - 1:
    For j from 0 to size - 1:
    If i is equal to j:
    Add 1.0 to data
    Otherwise:
    Add 0.0 to data
    Return data

Process called "create_zero_data" that takes rows as Integer and cols as Integer returns List[Any]:
    Let data be list containing
    For i from 0 to rows multiplied by cols - 1:
    Add 0.0 to data
    Return data

Process called "swap_matrix_rows" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and row1 as Integer and row2 as Integer:
    Let cols be matrix.shape at index 1
    For j from 0 to cols - 1:
    Let temp be matrix.data at index (row1 multiplied by cols j)
    Set matrix.data at index (row1 multiplied by cols j) to matrix.data at index (row2 multiplied by cols j)
    Set matrix.data at index (row2 multiplied by cols j) to temp

Process called "swap_matrix_rows_data" that takes data as List[Any] and row1 as Integer and row2 as Integer and cols as Integer:
    For j from 0 to cols - 1:
    Let temp be data at index (row1 multiplied by cols j)
    Set data at index (row1 multiplied by cols j) to data at index (row2 multiplied by cols j)
    Set data at index (row2 multiplied by cols j) to temp

Process called "determinant_3x3" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let a be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 0
    Let b be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 1
    Let c be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 2
    Let d be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 3
    Let e be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 4
    Let f be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 5
    Let g be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 6
    Let h be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 7
    Let i be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 8 Return a multiplied by (e multiplied by i - f multiplied by h) minus b multiplied by (d multiplied by i - f multiplied by g) c multiplied by (d multiplied by h - e multiplied by g)

Process called "determinant_lu" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let lu_result be lu_decomposition with matrix as matrix Match lu_result:
    When LUResult with l as l_matrix and u as u_matrix and p as p_matrix:
    Let det be 1.0
    Let n be u_matrix.shape at index 0 For i from 0 to n - 1:
    Let diagonal_val be Float.from with value as u_matrix.data at index (i multiplied by n i)
    Set det to det multiplied by diagonal_val Return det
    Otherwise:
    Return 0.0

Process called "inverse_2x2" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and det as Float returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let a be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 0
    Let b be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 1
    Let c be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 2
    Let d be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 3 Let inv_det be 1.0 divided by det Let result_data be list containing d multiplied by inv_det, (0.0 - b) multiplied by inv_det, (0.0 - c) multiplied by inv_det, a multiplied by inv_det Return NDArray.create_array with data as result_data and dtype as matrix.dtype and shape as matrix.shape

Process called "inverse_gauss_jordan" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let n be matrix.shape at index 0 Note: Create augmented matrix [A|I]
    Let augmented_data be list containing
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
    For j from 0 to 2 multiplied by n - 1:
    If j is less than n:
    Add matrix.data at index (i multiplied by n j) to augmented_data
    Otherwise:
    Let identity_col be j - n
    If i is equal to identity_col:
    Add 1.0 to augmented_data
    Otherwise:
    Add 0.0 to augmented_data Note: Gauss-Jordan elimination
    For pivot from 0 to n - 1:
    Note: Find pivot element and swap rows if necessary
    Let max_row be pivot
    Let max_val be Math.abs with x as Float.from with value as augmented_data at index (pivot multiplied by 2 multiplied by n pivot) For i from pivot 1 to n - 1:
    Let current_val be Math.abs with x as Float.from with value as augmented_data at index (i multiplied by 2 multiplied by n pivot)
    If current_val is greater than max_val:
    Set max_val to current_val
    Set max_row to i If max_row is not equal to pivot:
    For j from 0 to 2 multiplied by n - 1:
    Let temp be augmented_data at index (pivot multiplied by 2 multiplied by n j)
    Set augmented_data at index (pivot multiplied by 2 multiplied by n j) to augmented_data at index (max_row multiplied by 2 multiplied by n j)
    Set augmented_data at index (max_row multiplied by 2 multiplied by n j) to temp Note: Scale pivot row
    Let pivot_val be Float.from with value as augmented_data at index (pivot multiplied by 2 multiplied by n pivot) If Math.abs with x as pivot_val is less than 1e-12:
    Return NDArray.zeros with shape as matrix.shape and dtype as matrix.dtype For j from 0 to 2 multiplied by n - 1:
    Let current_val be Float.from with value as augmented_data at index (pivot multiplied by 2 multiplied by n j)
    Set augmented_data at index (pivot multiplied by 2 multiplied by n j) to current_val divided by pivot_val Note: Eliminate other rows
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
    If i is not equal to pivot:
    Let factor be Float.from with value as augmented_data at index (i multiplied by 2 multiplied by n pivot)
    For j from 0 to 2 multiplied by n - 1:
    Let row_val be Float.from with value as augmented_data at index (i multiplied by 2 multiplied by n j)
    Let pivot_val be Float.from with value as augmented_data at index (pivot multiplied by 2 multiplied by n j)
    Set augmented_data at index (i multiplied by 2 multiplied by n j) to row_val - factor multiplied by pivot_val Note: Extract inverse matrix
    Let inverse_data be list containing
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
    For j from n to 2 multiplied by n - 1:
    Add augmented_data at index (i multiplied by 2 multiplied by n j) to inverse_data Return NDArray.create_array with data as inverse_data and dtype as matrix.dtype and shape as matrix.shape

Note: Specialized solver implementations
Process called "solve_lu" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns LinearSystemResult:
    Let lu_result be lu_decomposition with matrix as a Match lu_result:
    When LUResult with l as l_matrix and u as u_matrix and p as p_matrix:
    Note: Solve Ly = Pb using forward substitution
    Let pb be matrix_vector_multiply with a as p_matrix and b as b
    Let y = forward_substitution with l as l_matrix and b as pb Note: Solve Ux = y using back substitution
    Let x = back_substitution with u as u_matrix and b as y Let residual = calculate_residual with a as a and x as x and b as b Return LinearSystemResult with:
    solution as x
    residual as residual
    rank as matrix_rank with matrix as a and tolerance as 1e-12
    singular as Math.abs with x as matrix_determinant with matrix as a is less than 1e-12
    condition_number as matrix_condition_number with matrix as a
    iterations as 1
    converged as true
    error_estimate as residual
    Otherwise:
    Return LinearSystemResult with:
    solution as NDArray.zeros with shape as b.shape and dtype as b.dtype
    residual as 0.0
    rank as 0
    singular as true
    condition_number as 0.0
    iterations as 0
    converged as false
    error_estimate as 0.0

Process called "solve_qr" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns LinearSystemResult:
    Let qr_result be qr_decomposition with matrix as a Match qr_result:
    When QRResult with q as q_matrix and r as r_matrix:
    Let qt_b be matrix_vector_multiply with a as matrix_transpose with matrix as q_matrix and b as b
    Let x be back_substitution with u as r_matrix and b as qt_b
    Let residual be calculate_residual with a as a and x as x and b as b Return LinearSystemResult with:
    solution as x
    residual as residual
    rank as matrix_rank with matrix as a and tolerance as 1e-12
    singular as false
    condition_number as matrix_condition_number with matrix as a
    iterations as 1
    converged as true
    error_estimate as residual
    Otherwise:
    Return LinearSystemResult with:
    solution as NDArray.zeros with shape as b.shape and dtype as b.dtype
    residual as 0.0
    rank as 0
    singular as true
    condition_number as 0.0
    iterations as 0
    converged as false
    error_estimate as 0.0

Process called "solve_cholesky" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns LinearSystemResult:
    Let chol_result be cholesky_decomposition with matrix as a Match chol_result:
    When CholeskyResult with l as l_matrix:
    Let y be forward_substitution with l as l_matrix and b as b
    Let lt_matrix be matrix_transpose with matrix as l_matrix
    Let x be back_substitution with u as lt_matrix and b as y
    Let residual be calculate_residual with a as a and x as x and b as b Return LinearSystemResult with:
    solution as x
    residual as residual
    rank as matrix_rank with matrix as a and tolerance as 1e-12
    singular as false
    condition_number as matrix_condition_number with matrix as a
    iterations as 1
    converged as true
    error_estimate as residual
    Otherwise:
    Return LinearSystemResult with:
    solution as NDArray.zeros with shape as b.shape and dtype as b.dtype
    residual as 0.0
    rank as 0
    singular as true
    condition_number as 0.0
    iterations as 0
    converged as false
    error_estimate as 0.0

Note: Triangular system solvers
Process called "forward_substitution" that takes l as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let n be l.shape at index 0
    Let solution_data be list containing For i from 0 to n - 1:
    Add 0.0 to solution_data For i from 0 to n - 1:
    Let sum be 0.0
    For j from 0 to i - 1:
    Let l_ij be Float.from with value as l.data at index (i multiplied by n j)
    Let x_j be Float.from with value as solution_data at index j
    Set sum to sum l_ij multiplied by x_j Let b_i be Float.from with value as b.data at index i
    Let l_ii be Float.from with value as l.data at index (i multiplied by n i) If Math.abs with x as l_ii is greater than 1e-12:
    Set solution_data at index i to (b_i - sum) divided by l_ii
    Otherwise:
    Set solution_data at index i to 0.0 Return NDArray.create_array with data as solution_data and dtype as b.dtype and shape as b.shape

Process called "back_substitution" that takes u as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let n be u.shape at index 0
    Let solution_data be list containing For i from 0 to n - 1:
    Add 0.0 to solution_data For i from n - 1 down to 0:
    Let sum be 0.0
    For j from i 1 to n - 1:
    Let u_ij be Float.from with value as u.data at index (i multiplied by n j)
    Let x_j be Float.from with value as solution_data at index j
    Set sum to sum u_ij multiplied by x_j Let b_i be Float.from with value as b.data at index i
    Let u_ii be Float.from with value as u.data at index (i multiplied by n i) If Math.abs with x as u_ii is greater than 1e-12:
    Set solution_data at index i to (b_i - sum) divided by u_ii
    Otherwise:
    Set solution_data at index i to 0.0 Return NDArray.create_array with data as solution_data and dtype as b.dtype and shape as b.shape

Process called "calculate_residual" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and x as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let ax be matrix_vector_multiply with a as a and b as x
    Let residual_sum be 0.0 For i from 0 to b.size - 1:
    Let ax_val be Float.from with value as ax.data at index i
    Let b_val be Float.from with value as b.data at index i
    Let diff be ax_val - b_val
    Set residual_sum to residual_sum diff multiplied by diff Return Math.sqrt with x as residual_sum

Process called "matrix_vector_multiply" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    If a.ndim is not equal to 2 or b.ndim is not equal to 1:
    Return NDArray.zeros with shape as b.shape and dtype as b.dtype Let m be a.shape at index 0
    Let n be a.shape at index 1 If n is not equal to b.size:
    Return NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing m and dtype as b.dtype Let result_data be list containing
    For i from 0 to m - 1:
    Let sum be 0.0
    For j from 0 to n - 1:
    Let a_val be Float.from with value as a.data at index (i multiplied by n j)
    Let b_val be Float.from with value as b.data at index j
    Set sum to sum a_val multiplied by b_val
    Add sum to result_data Return NDArray.create_array with data as result_data and dtype as b.dtype and shape as list containing m

Note: Specialized eigenvalue computations
Process called "eigenvalues_2x2" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray returns DecompositionResult:
    Let a be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 0
    Let b be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 1
    Let c be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 2
    Let d be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index 3 Let trace be a d
    Let determinant be a multiplied by d - b multiplied by c
    Let discriminant be trace multiplied by trace - 4.0 multiplied by determinant Let eigenval1 be (trace Math.sqrt with x as discriminant) divided by 2.0
    Let eigenval2 be (trace - Math.sqrt with x as discriminant) divided by 2.0 Let eigenvals_data be list containing eigenval1, eigenval2
    Let eigenvals be NDArray.create_array with data as eigenvals_data and dtype as matrix.dtype and shape as list containing 2 Note: Compute eigenvectors
    Let eigenvecs_data be list containing 1.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0
    If Math.abs with x as b is greater than 1e-12:
    Set eigenvecs_data at index 0 to eigenval1 - d
    Set eigenvecs_data at index 1 to b
    Set eigenvecs_data at index 2 to eigenval2 - d
    Set eigenvecs_data at index 3 to b
    Otherwise if Math.abs with x as c is greater than 1e-12:
    Set eigenvecs_data at index 0 to c
    Set eigenvecs_data at index 1 to eigenval1 - a
    Set eigenvecs_data at index 2 to c
    Set eigenvecs_data at index 3 to eigenval2 - a Let eigenvecs be NDArray.create_array with data as eigenvecs_data and dtype as matrix.dtype and shape as list containing 2, 2 Return EigenResult with eigenvalues as eigenvals and eigenvectors as eigenvecs

Process called "eigenvalues_qr_algorithm" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and max_iterations as Integer returns DecompositionResult:
    Let a = NDArray.copy_array with arr as matrix
    Let n = a.shape at index 0 Note: QR algorithm iterations
    For iteration from 0 to max_iterations - 1:
    Let qr_result be qr_decomposition with matrix as a Match qr_result:
    When QRResult with q as q_matrix and r as r_matrix:
    Set a to matrix_multiply with a as r_matrix and b as q_matrix
    Otherwise:
    Break Note: Check for convergence (simplified)
    Let off_diagonal_norm be 0.0
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
    For j from 0 to n - 1:
    If i is not equal to j:
    Let val be Float.from with value as a.data at index (i multiplied by n j)
    Set off_diagonal_norm to off_diagonal_norm val multiplied by val If off_diagonal_norm is less than 1e-12:
    Break Note: Extract eigenvalues from diagonal
    Let eigenvals_data be list containing
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
    Add a.data at index (i multiplied by n i) to eigenvals_data Let eigenvals be NDArray.create_array with data as eigenvals_data and dtype as matrix.dtype and shape as list containing n
    Let eigenvecs be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n, n and dtype as matrix.dtype Return EigenResult with eigenvalues as eigenvals and eigenvectors as eigenvecs